20th Level - Swooping Strike			KEY:Totem Warrior (Hawk) ~ Swooping Strike				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:(Ex)Totem Warrior Class Feature.SpecialQuality						DESC:While flying, a hawk totem warrior can make a charge attack that inflicts damage as if the weapon inflicted a critical hit—even if striking a foe normally immune to critical hits. If the swooping strike attack inflicts an actual critical hit, increase the critical’s multiplier by +1; thus, a longsword inflicts a × 3 critical hit, while a greataxe inflicts a × 4 critical hit. If the swooping strike attack misses, the ability is still considered used for that day. A swooping strike does not trigger special effects that occur only when critical hits occur, such as the decapitating power of a vorpal weapon. The hawk totem warrior can use this ability only once per day for every point of her Dexterity bonus (minimum once per day).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.82
